>>> Computer Networks (Atul) Sunil S Shah

Computer Networks by Atul Kahate and Sunil S. Shah is a comprehensive textbook that covers the fundamental concepts and principles of computer networks. The book provides an in-depth understanding of the architecture, design, and implementation of computer networks
The book starts with a brief introduction to the field of computer networks, followed by an overview of the different types of networks, such as local area networks (LANs), wide area networks (WANs), and metropolitan area networks (MANs). It then covers the basics of network protocols, including the Internet Protocol (IP), Transmission Control Protocol (TCP), and User Datagram Protocol (UDP).
The book also includes a discussion of the various layers of the OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) model, including the physical layer, data link layer, network layer, transport layer, and application layer. The book provides a comprehensive overview of routing algorithms and congestion control, as well as network security, including firewalls, intrusion detection systems, and encryption.
The authors also cover advanced topics in computer networks, such as Quality of Service (QoS), multimedia networks, and wireless networks. The book includes numerous examples and case studies to illustrate key concepts and techniques, and provides practical tips for network administrators and engineers.
Overall, Computer Networks by Atul Kahate and Sunil S. Shah is an excellent resource for students, professionals, and anyone interested in learning about the fundamentals of computer networks. With its clear explanations, practical examples, and comprehensive coverage of the field, this book is an ideal starting point for those looking to build a career in computer networking or to simply expand their knowledge of the subject.

